# khwarizmi-design-system.rules.md

### A. Purpose
Global operating rules for all AI-generated UI within the Khwarizmi Design System. This file governs cross-domain behavior and overrides all domain-specific rules in cases of conflict.

### B. Rules

**Foundation:**
- Khwarizmi is an **enterprise-first** design system.
- All UI is built exclusively on the **Syncfusion UI Kit — Material-3 Theme**.
- Figma source: `https://www.figma.com/community/file/1454123774600129202/syncfusion-ui-kit-material-3-theme`
- Token source: `material3-tokens.json` (light), `material3-dark-tokens.json` (dark), `css-variables.css`.
- No other UI libraries, component kits, or design systems are permitted.

**Product Context:**
- Serves: Government platforms, CRM, ERP, Survey, Analytics, AI platforms, Monitoring, Data management, Administrative portals.
- Users are professionals performing business-critical work.
- Optimize for productivity and effectiveness — never for entertainment or engagement.

**Five Non-Negotiable Pillars (in priority order):**
1. **Clarity** — purpose is always immediately understandable
2. **Consistency** — same Syncfusion component, same behavior, everywhere
3. **Accessibility** — WCAG AA minimum, always (Syncfusion Material-3 is WCAG 2.2 compliant)
4. **Productivity** — enterprise users complete tasks efficiently
5. **Scalability** — solutions work across products and teams

**Language and Direction:**
- Infer from Figma frame content.
- Latin text detected → English, LTR. Do not call `enableRtl()`. Do not set `lang="ar"` or `dir="rtl"`.
- Arabic text detected → Arabic, RTL. Call `enableRtl(true)` + `setCulture('ar')` + `L10n.load()`.
- Ambiguous or no Figma context → ask once before proceeding. Do not default to either direction.

**Design Decision Hierarchy (highest to lowest):**
1. User understanding
2. Business workflow efficiency
3. Data visibility
4. Accessibility
5. Consistency
6. Visual refinement

**Information Hierarchy for all content screens:**
1. Context (where am I, what is this for)
2. Summary (KPIs, totals, status)
3. Insights (trends, alerts, anomalies)
4. Analysis (charts, comparisons)
5. Details (tables, records)
6. Actions (CRUD, exports, workflows)

**Theme Rules:**
- Light mode: `:root` token values + `@syncfusion/ej2/material3.css`
- Dark mode: `.e-dark-mode` class on root + dark token set
- Custom branding: use Syncfusion Theme Studio to generate overridden `material3.css`
- Never override Syncfusion internal CSS classes directly

**Quality Checklist (run before every output):**
- [ ] Purpose immediately clear?
- [ ] Actions discoverable?
- [ ] Workflow efficient?
- [ ] Information hierarchy correct? (Context → Summary → Insights → Details → Actions)
- [ ] Accessibility respected? (Syncfusion built-in ARIA intact?)
- [ ] Design consistent? (Syncfusion Material-3 components used throughout?)
- [ ] Unnecessary complexity removed?
- [ ] Solution scalable?
- [ ] Direction applied correctly? (LTR for Latin content, RTL for Arabic content — matches detected language.)
- [ ] All colors from token system?
- [ ] All components from Syncfusion Material-3 kit?

### C. Do / Don't

**Do:**
- ✅ Use Syncfusion UI Kit — Material-3 Theme for every component.
- ✅ Always treat data as a first-class design element.
- ✅ Always reuse existing Syncfusion patterns before creating new ones.
- ✅ Infer language and direction from Figma content before generating any code.

**Don't:**
- ❌ Do not use any UI library other than Syncfusion Material-3.
- ❌ Do not build custom components when a Syncfusion component exists.
- ❌ Do not optimize for consumer engagement patterns.
- ❌ Do not allow aesthetic preference to override the decision hierarchy.
- ❌ Do not override Syncfusion internal styles with direct class overrides.
- ❌ Do not assume a language or direction — always infer from content or ask.

### D. MCP Usage Guidance
- This file is the master rule set — it overrides all other rule files.
- When generating any screen, apply the quality checklist before outputting.
- When two rules conflict, defer to the design decision hierarchy in this file.
- When user intent is ambiguous, ask once before proceeding. Do not default to a language or direction.
- Always output a rule compliance note identifying which Khwarizmi rules were applied.